    "question_id" : 79803868,
    "title" : "How to run a SQL script in Java NOT on startup?",
    "body" : "<p>I have a Spring application which is multi-tenant (uses JdbcTemplate for data access). There are several tables creates for each tenant, and I want to keep this SQL code in a separate <code>init_tenant.sql</code> script. For each tenant created, I create a schema in MySQL, so I need to run SQL init code <strong>while</strong> the app is running, and not on startup.</p>\n<p>I can't use <code>JdbcTemplate.execute</code> since it only works with a single statement.</p>\n<p>I have not found a way to run a SQL script NOT in the startup of the application.</p>\n<p>Any suggestions?</p>\n",
